## Limitations

The findings are based on available literature and expert opinions, which may not fully capture the rapidly evolving nature of robotics technology. Additionally, the impact of robots on quality of life can vary significantly across different regions and industries, depending on factors such as economic conditions, regulatory environments, and cultural attitudes towards technology. Further empirical research is needed to quantify the long-term effects of robotics on quality of life.

